Most Blue Cars API
Overview
The Most Blue Cars API is a simple RESTful service that identifies the most common blue car model from a dataset. This API can be used to analyze color-specific data, making it valuable for businesses and organizations interested in marketing, inventory management, and logistics.

Features
Filter by Color: Filters a dataset to focus on cars that are blue.
Aggregation: Counts occurrences of each blue car model to identify the most common one.
Simple Integration: Easy to integrate with other services via RESTful endpoints.
Installation
To set up and run the API locally, follow these steps:

Clone the Repository:

bash
git clone https://github.com/ngwenyawiseman/car-crud-api.git
cd most-blue-cars-api
Install Dependencies:
Make sure you have Node.js installed, then run:

bash
Copy code
npm install
Run the Server:
Start the API server:

bash
npm start
Access the API:
The API will be available at http://localhost:3000.

Endpoints
GET /most-blue-cars
Description: Returns the most common blue car model in the dataset.
Response:
200 OK: A JSON object with the most common blue car model.
Example:
json
Copy code
{
  "model": "Toyota Corolla",
  "count": 35
}
Usage
You can interact with the API using tools like curl, Postman, or any HTTP client. For example:

bash
curl -X GET http://localhost:3000/most-blue-cars
This command will return the most popular blue car model in the dataset.

Technology Stack
Node.js: Backend runtime environment.
Express.js: Web framework for building RESTful APIs.
Mocha: Test framework for running unit tests.
Chai: Assertion library for testing.
Testing
The API includes a suite of unit tests using Mocha and Chai. To run the tests, use the following command:

bash
npm test
